    <note type="dates"><date>1814–84</date></note>
    
    <note type="biography">
        <p>Novelist and playwright. BA, Oxford (Magdalen College), 1835; fellow, 1836–84. Studied law from 1835; called to the bar, 1842. Author of <hi rend="italic">The cloister and the hearth</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Hard cash</hi>, and the play <hi rend="italic">It’s never too late to mend.</hi> Known for social realism, sensationalism, and melodrama.</p></note>
